accd -- ACC dedicated server reimplementation (work in progress)

Placeholder name.  Rename to whatever you like.

This is a clean-room reimplementation of the Assetto Corsa Competizione
dedicated server, built so an unmodified ACC game client can connect
and play a private multiplayer session without any traffic to Kunos's
backend.  See ../notebook-b/NOTEBOOK_B.md for the protocol
specification this code is working towards.

STATUS
    Phase 0 skeleton.  Binds the configured TCP and UDP listening
    sockets and logs every byte received with a hex dump.  No protocol
    interpretation yet.

BUILD
    make

    Tested on Linux (aarch64, Debian sid).  Intended to also build on
    OpenBSD without changes -- iconv is in libc on both platforms and
    there are no GNU-isms in the source or the Makefile.

RUN
    The server expects cfg/configuration.json (UTF-16 LE) in its
    current working directory, matching the Kunos server layout.
    Easiest way is to run it from the stock server's directory:

        cd /path/to/acc-server/server
        /path/to/accd/accd

    It will print the parsed config, bind the configured ports, and
    log every byte received until interrupted (Ctrl-C).  On OpenBSD
    the process pledges "stdio inet" after the ports are bound.

    To test without a real client:

        nc -u 127.0.0.1 $udpPort   # UDP test
        nc    127.0.0.1 $tcpPort   # TCP test

STYLE
    Portable C99.  libc only.  KNF-ish with 4-space indents.
    err(3)/errx(3) for fatal errors, sigaction(2) not signal(3),
    pledge(2) on OpenBSD.  No dynamic allocation in the hot paths.
